1
00:01:53,459 --> 00:01:54,260
Professor Fan

2
00:01:54,739 --> 00:01:55,859
Since you got sick,

3
00:01:55,859 --> 00:01:56,700
you've lost weight.

4
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:58,060
You're skin and bones.

5
00:01:58,060 --> 00:01:59,260
You're so thin you're unrecognizable.

6
00:01:59,540 --> 00:02:00,780
Don't you think so, Yingzi?

7
00:02:01,140 --> 00:02:02,219
Not really.

8
00:02:02,420 --> 00:02:04,500
I actually think Professor Fan has gained weight.

9
00:02:04,739 --> 00:02:05,819
Probably from the illness.

10
00:02:05,819 --> 00:02:07,219
Edema. Puffiness.

11
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,419
I don't think any of you are right.

12
00:02:09,460 --> 00:02:10,419
Professor Fan,

13
00:02:10,419 --> 00:02:12,500
his weight hasn't changed much.

14
00:02:12,620 --> 00:02:14,099
It's mainly his vitality.

15
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,860
One look and you can tell he's not doing well.

16
00:02:15,860 --> 00:02:17,020
He looks exhausted.

17
00:02:17,020 --> 00:02:18,500
You look completely sickly.

18
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:19,259
Zhu Zhu!

19
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:20,740
What are you saying?

20
00:02:21,580 --> 00:02:22,500
Grandpa Fan,

21
00:02:22,580 --> 00:02:24,340
he's using the wrong words.

22
00:02:24,580 --> 00:02:25,379
I think,

23
00:02:25,379 --> 00:02:27,580
you shouldn't call this a sickly state.

24
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:29,580
It should be called a sickly appearance.

25
00:02:29,819 --> 00:02:31,699
Then you might as well call it a smoker's face.

26
00:02:31,939 --> 00:02:33,819
But Professor Fan doesn't smoke.

27
00:02:34,939 --> 00:02:36,419
Students,

28
00:02:36,740 --> 00:02:37,900
actually, my illness...

29
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:39,139
is already cured.

30
00:02:40,219 --> 00:02:40,840
So fast?

31
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:41,219
Yes.

32
00:02:41,939 --> 00:02:43,560
Then you still need to rest and recover.

33
00:02:43,699 --> 00:02:44,939
Stop writing all the time.

34
00:02:44,939 --> 00:02:46,780
Exactly. Turn off the computer for Mr. Fan.

35
00:02:47,479 --> 00:02:49,259
I haven't saved it yet!

36
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:50,219
Students,

37
00:02:50,659 --> 00:02:51,539
it's getting late.

38
00:02:51,539 --> 00:02:52,639
We should go back to the dorm.

39
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:54,419
Let's not disturb Professor Fan's rest.

40
00:02:54,539 --> 00:02:55,900
Aren't you leaving yet?

41
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:56,580
No...

42
00:02:56,740 --> 00:02:58,080
I mean, thank you guys.

43
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:58,840
Hurry up and go.

44
00:02:59,340 --> 00:02:59,919
No,

45
00:03:00,139 --> 00:03:00,780
take care.

46
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:01,379
I won't see you out.

47
00:03:01,379 --> 00:03:02,740
But as soon as we leave,

48
00:03:02,740 --> 00:03:05,099
Professor Fan will start writing again.

49
00:03:05,099 --> 00:03:05,939
What should we do?

50
00:03:06,259 --> 00:03:07,060
How about this?

51
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:08,340
I'll stay and take care of him for a couple of days.

52
00:03:08,340 --> 00:03:09,280
And supervise him while I'm at it.

53
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,159
Don't.

54
00:03:10,159 --> 00:03:11,860
What kind of rotten idea is that?

55
00:03:12,180 --> 00:03:13,699
Where would you sleep if you stayed?

56
00:03:13,979 --> 00:03:16,460
Yangliu Xincheng Retirement Community has rules.

57
00:03:16,580 --> 00:03:18,219
No overnight guests allowed. Right.

58
00:03:18,379 --> 00:03:19,560
So your idea won't work at all.

59
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,000
It won't work.

60
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:20,560
It won't work.

61
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:20,900
Let's go.

62
00:03:20,979 --> 00:03:21,860
Let's just...

63
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:22,939
take Professor Fan's computer...

64
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:23,919
away, wouldn't that work?

65
00:03:23,919 --> 00:03:24,340
Don't!

66
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:24,960
No!

67
00:03:25,219 --> 00:03:26,379
Never heard of such a thing.

68
00:03:26,379 --> 00:03:28,580
Why would you take Grandpa Fan's computer?

69
00:03:28,979 --> 00:03:30,259
Exactly. Just unplug the power cord.

70
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:31,219
Don't! You... No!

71
00:03:31,219 --> 00:03:32,139
Sorry, Mr. Fan.

72
00:03:32,139 --> 00:03:33,419
To let you rest and recover in peace,

73
00:03:33,419 --> 00:03:35,699
we'll keep this power cord for a week.

74
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:36,699
Hey, Zhu Zhu,

75
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,939
you're a grown-up,

76
00:03:38,939 --> 00:03:40,259
why are you acting so childish?

77
00:03:40,259 --> 00:03:40,939
Yeah.

78
00:03:40,939 --> 00:03:41,979
Is this how you handle things?

79
00:03:41,979 --> 00:03:42,860
You can't do that.

80
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:44,539
Is just pulling the cord enough?

81
00:03:44,539 --> 00:03:45,500
Then what should we do?

82
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:46,939
You have to take the battery too.

83
00:03:46,939 --> 00:03:47,580
Don't!

84
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:48,780
You're right.

85
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:49,500
Professor Fan,

86
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,300
you rest for now.

87
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:52,020
We'll come see you another day.

88
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:53,060
Bye, Grandpa Fan.

89
00:03:53,060 --> 00:03:53,719
Bye, Mr. Fan.

90
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:55,139
Bye-bye now!

91
00:03:55,699 --> 00:03:56,699
Come back!

92
00:03:57,259 --> 00:03:58,659
Give me my stuff!

93
00:04:01,659 --> 00:04:02,460
Come back!

94
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:08,659
What's going on with you guys?

95
00:04:11,979 --> 00:04:13,020
Little Li.

96
00:04:14,340 --> 00:04:16,379
How is your skit coming along?

97
00:04:16,699 --> 00:04:17,399
It's a disaster.

98
00:04:17,980 --> 00:04:18,819
Just miserable.

99
00:04:19,540 --> 00:04:20,500
As expected.

100
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:22,180
We even made it to the semi-finals.

101
00:04:22,699 --> 00:04:23,899
The busier it gets...

102
00:04:24,139 --> 00:04:25,019
...the more trouble it is.

103
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:28,439
Your skit performed pretty well too.

104
00:04:28,439 --> 00:04:30,680
As soon as you went on stage, you triggered...

105
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,160
...prolonged and unceasing...

106
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:32,879
Listen to this.

107
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:33,680
...crying.

108
00:04:35,839 --> 00:04:37,019
And have already been gloriously...

109
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:39,439
...eliminated.

110
00:04:40,819 --> 00:04:41,279
You...

111
00:04:41,279 --> 00:04:43,879
You really have a sharp tongue, kid.

112
00:04:44,639 --> 00:04:46,519
Getting eliminated...

113
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:47,839
...wasn't a big deal.

114
00:04:47,839 --> 00:04:49,160
But the way you put it...

115
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,519
...makes me want to cry.

116
00:04:51,519 --> 00:04:53,920
Your skit was indeed very touching.

117
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:57,040
But this competition is for comedy skits.

118
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,480
You guys turned it into a tragedy.

119
00:04:59,759 --> 00:05:01,079
Do you think that could get a high score?

120
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,139
Let's go.

121
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,240
We won't give certain people...

122
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,040
...a chance to humblebrag. Let's go.

123
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,120
Have you two finished eating?

124
00:05:14,959 --> 00:05:15,759
Professor Fan

125
00:05:16,079 --> 00:05:17,240
It's been a whole day.

126
00:05:17,319 --> 00:05:18,180
Hard work.

127
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,079
What do you want to eat?

128
00:05:19,079 --> 00:05:19,759
I'll go get it for you.

129
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:20,600
Eat what?

130
00:05:20,879 --> 00:05:22,079
I'm full from anger.

131
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:24,040
Who is it this time?

132
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:25,399
Who else but you?

133
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:26,120
With you.

134
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,160
I didn't mess with you today.

135
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:30,120
I didn't write a single word again today.

136
00:05:30,319 --> 00:05:31,720
Just because you didn't write a word,

137
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,560
why are you taking it out on me?

138
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,720
If not for that lousy idea you gave me,

139
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,720
telling me to fake being sick,

140
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,519
would it have ended up like this?

141
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,120
Today was just great.

142
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:42,399
Three waves of visitors came by.

143
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,199
Bringing flowers and fruit.

144
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:47,199
It seems that for this problem,

145
00:05:47,199 --> 00:05:48,879
I should take the main responsibility.

146
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:49,240
Right.

147
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:51,279
Whoever tied the bell must untie it.

148
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,160
I'll help you solve it.

149
00:05:53,399 --> 00:05:55,199
You solve it? How?

150
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:56,600
Take the flowers that were sent,

151
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,240
and give a bunch to every room.

152
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:00,240
No need to worry about the leftover fruit.

153
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,680
I will help you

154
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,040
finish it off.

155
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:05,199
In your dreams.

156
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,720
Do I need you to solve that?

157
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,720
I spent the whole day just greeting guests.

158
00:06:10,879 --> 00:06:11,800
I didn't write a single word.

159
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,439
This problem hasn't been solved.

160
00:06:13,839 --> 00:06:15,639
And those college student volunteers,

161
00:06:15,639 --> 00:06:17,959
they almost took my power cord and battery.

162
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,920
I had to chase them all over.

163
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:22,040
Look how much time I wasted today.

164
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,699
Don't be so anxious.

165
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,500
You have to look at both sides of the issue.

166
00:06:26,899 --> 00:06:28,459
Use dialectics.

167
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:30,860
On the surface,

168
00:06:31,259 --> 00:06:32,540
time was indeed wasted.

169
00:06:32,660 --> 00:06:33,660
But in reality?

170
00:06:34,660 --> 00:06:35,540
It was wasted.

171
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:36,860
Isn't that nonsense?

172
00:06:37,019 --> 00:06:39,060
Although time was wasted,

173
00:06:39,579 --> 00:06:40,699
what about the progress?

174
00:06:41,699 --> 00:06:42,660
Of course, that was delayed too.

175
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:43,860
That's still nonsense.

176
00:06:43,959 --> 00:06:44,660
Look at you.

177
00:06:44,660 --> 00:06:45,540
Getting anxious again.

178
00:06:45,939 --> 00:06:48,019
Aren't I helping you figure this out?

179
00:06:48,019 --> 00:06:49,420
Why did I tell you to fake being sick?

180
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:52,019
Wasn't it because you get too many calls?

181
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:53,220
Yes, that's true.

182
00:06:53,660 --> 00:06:55,459
Then I have to ask.

183
00:06:56,139 --> 00:06:56,980
Why do people

184
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:59,180
call you all the time?

185
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:01,100
They want me to give lectures,

186
00:07:01,339 --> 00:07:02,300
attend seminars,

187
00:07:02,579 --> 00:07:03,740
or commission book drafts.

188
00:07:04,019 --> 00:07:05,540
Oh, and they want me on TV

189
00:07:05,579 --> 00:07:06,339
as a guest.

190
00:07:06,939 --> 00:07:08,579
Your main job right now

191
00:07:08,579 --> 00:07:10,500
is to finish your manuscript.

192
00:07:10,939 --> 00:07:12,259
How do you have the time

193
00:07:12,259 --> 00:07:14,019
for so many social activities?

194
00:07:15,860 --> 00:07:16,939
Refusing them outright

195
00:07:17,939 --> 00:07:19,160
is definitely out of the question.

196
00:07:19,959 --> 00:07:20,759
Throwing away your phone,

197
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:22,779
you definitely wouldn't like that.

198
00:07:22,779 --> 00:07:23,459
Sigh.

199
00:07:23,660 --> 00:07:24,579
I told you to fake being sick,

200
00:07:24,939 --> 00:07:26,899
but then all those visitors came.

201
00:07:28,139 --> 00:07:29,139
I say we just...

202
00:07:31,339 --> 00:07:32,500
You go hide out of town.

203
00:07:34,699 --> 00:07:35,939
Now you get it, right?

204
00:07:36,459 --> 00:07:38,420
I don't mean for you to actually go out of town.

205
00:07:39,139 --> 00:07:39,819
I get it.

206
00:07:39,819 --> 00:07:41,459
You mean physically, I...

207
00:07:41,939 --> 00:07:42,860
stay in Beijing to write.

208
00:07:42,860 --> 00:07:43,740
If there's a phone call,

209
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:45,060
I just say I'm out of town.

210
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:45,860
You want me to lie?

211
00:07:45,860 --> 00:07:46,319
Right?

212
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:46,860
Right.

213
00:07:47,699 --> 00:07:49,300
Don't make it sound so ugly.

214
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,379
This isn't called lying.

215
00:07:53,019 --> 00:07:54,699
It's called the art of language.

216
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:56,660
It's a white lie.

217
00:07:58,060 --> 00:08:00,180
It's different from regular lying.

218
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:01,100
You know?

219
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:02,139
Right.

220
00:08:02,139 --> 00:08:03,379
This is good for your creative work.

221
00:08:03,379 --> 00:08:03,920
Isn't it?

222
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:04,560
Yes.

223
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:08,060
If the person calling has something urgent,

224
00:08:08,060 --> 00:08:09,779
I'll just say I happen to be coming back tomorrow.

225
00:08:09,779 --> 00:08:10,660
If it's nothing urgent,

226
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:12,139
I'll say I can't come back tomorrow.

227
00:08:12,740 --> 00:08:13,540
I have to say,

228
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,579
you, Professor Fan, regarding talking nonsense...

229
00:08:15,579 --> 00:08:16,300
No.

230
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:18,019
Lying.

231
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,579
White lies.

232
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:21,699
The art of language.

233
00:08:22,459 --> 00:08:23,819
You catch on pretty fast.

234
00:08:23,819 --> 00:08:25,779
Shows you have a real talent for this.

235
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:27,540
Isn't that still just talking nonsense?

236
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:29,579
It's not talking nonsense.

237
00:08:29,579 --> 00:08:30,379
It's a lie...

238
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:32,659
It's the art of language.

239
00:08:33,379 --> 00:08:34,179
Same thing.

240
00:08:35,139 --> 00:08:38,139
Why are you intellectuals so pedantic?

241
00:08:38,659 --> 00:08:40,740
If someone invites you to a symposium,

242
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:41,980
invites you to give a speech,

243
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:44,299
and you don't go, it hurts their feelings.

244
00:08:44,340 --> 00:08:45,779
But if you do go,

245
00:08:46,059 --> 00:08:47,539
it delays your work.

246
00:08:47,539 --> 00:08:48,460
So what do you do?

247
00:08:49,059 --> 00:08:50,899
That... that really is a tough one.

248
00:08:50,899 --> 00:08:53,340
Exactly, so listening to me is the right move.

249
00:08:55,820 --> 00:08:56,620
This...

250
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:57,539
Pretty busy.

251
00:08:57,539 --> 00:08:58,299
Hello?

252
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:00,340
Editor Zhao.

253
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:01,059
Hello.

254
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:02,379
Sorry about that.

255
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:04,940
I've been really busy lately.

256
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:06,220
Say you're out of town!

257
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:07,940
Say you're out of town!

258
00:09:08,039 --> 00:09:08,779
No, no.

259
00:09:08,779 --> 00:09:10,419
It's me who is out of town.

260
00:09:10,779 --> 00:09:11,980
Where am I out of town?

261
00:09:12,299 --> 00:09:13,220
Where am I out of town?

262
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:14,179
Just say anywhere!

263
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:15,940
I'm in Shanxi.

264
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:17,940
Where in Shanxi?

265
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,100
Chengde, Shanxi.

266
00:09:19,139 --> 00:09:20,340
That's in Hebei!

267
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:21,899
I'm in Shanxi Hebei.

268
00:09:22,379 --> 00:09:24,059
No, I'm in Hebei Shanxi.

269
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:25,539
I...

270
00:09:25,539 --> 00:09:27,899
I'm in that... Chengde, Hebei.

271
00:09:28,379 --> 00:09:30,259
Getting old, the brain doesn't work so well.

272
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:32,820
Editor Zhao, what did you need me for?

273
00:09:33,860 --> 00:09:34,379
Oh.

274
00:09:35,019 --> 00:09:37,299
My "New Interpretation of Classical Poetry Metrics"?

275
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:38,220
It's been published?

276
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:39,259
Thank you.

277
00:09:39,259 --> 00:09:40,179
Thank you so much.

278
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:42,299
Then hurry up and send it over to me.

279
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:43,740
I have time.

280
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:45,659
You're in Chengde, how do you have time?

281
00:09:46,539 --> 00:09:48,019
Right, I'm in Chengde.

282
00:09:48,019 --> 00:09:48,460
Right?

283
00:09:50,940 --> 00:09:51,840
Alright then.

284
00:09:52,059 --> 00:09:52,659
Okay.

285
00:09:52,659 --> 00:09:53,860
We'll talk later then.

286
00:09:54,379 --> 00:09:55,179
Goodbye.

287
00:09:55,940 --> 00:09:57,580
So dumb, really dumb.

288
00:09:57,620 --> 00:09:58,500
It's all your fault.

289
00:09:58,580 --> 00:09:59,860
You insisted I say I was out of town.

290
00:10:00,059 --> 00:10:01,139
What was it this time?

291
00:10:01,259 --> 00:10:02,700
They wanted to bring me my royalties.

292
00:10:02,899 --> 00:10:04,059
So what?

293
00:10:04,059 --> 00:10:05,259
Just say you're coming back tomorrow.

294
00:10:05,259 --> 00:10:06,460
He'll bring the money over tomorrow.

295
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:07,419
Isn't that the best of both worlds?

296
00:10:07,419 --> 00:10:08,659
What "best of both worlds"?

297
00:10:08,860 --> 00:10:10,500
Their accountant is going on a business trip tomorrow.

298
00:10:12,379 --> 00:10:13,179
You tell me...

299
00:10:18,899 --> 00:10:19,360
Hello.

300
00:10:25,299 --> 00:10:26,379
It's miserable.

301
00:10:30,299 --> 00:10:32,000
Just miserable.

302
00:10:32,580 --> 00:10:34,700
We still have to go to the district for the finals.

303
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:36,659
So go participate.

304
00:10:37,340 --> 00:10:38,659
Who asked you?

305
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:41,100
You two...

306
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:43,059
Asked or not...

307
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:45,419
I made it to the finals too.

308
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:50,059
Speaking of which, it's really strange.

309
00:10:50,379 --> 00:10:52,559
That you can actually act.

310
00:10:54,539 --> 00:10:55,539
That's where you're clueless.

311
00:10:55,539 --> 00:10:57,139
I'm a professional.

312
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:58,659
An arts backbone.

313
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:00,779
Once I make a move,

314
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,899
I'm better than average.

315
00:11:02,299 --> 00:11:03,820
Who among average people can't act?

316
00:11:03,899 --> 00:11:05,019
Unless they're a fool.

317
00:11:06,259 --> 00:11:08,039
That's why I find it strange.

318
00:11:08,259 --> 00:11:10,259
That you can actually act.

319
00:11:10,259 --> 00:11:11,299
What do you mean "actually"?

320
00:11:12,299 --> 00:11:13,100
What does that mean?

321
00:11:13,659 --> 00:11:14,940
So you're saying I'm a fool?

322
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:17,059
You said that yourself.

323
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:19,820
This old pedant, hey.

324
00:11:20,019 --> 00:11:22,100
Unleashing your sharp tongue again.

325
00:11:22,740 --> 00:11:23,740
Let me tell you.

326
00:11:24,259 --> 00:11:26,580
I play the lead based on talent.

327
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:28,500
Based on my artistic sense.

328
00:11:28,659 --> 00:11:29,980
Based on Director Xiong from the theater,

329
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:32,139
Chasing me to praise my acting.

330
00:11:32,139 --> 00:11:33,659
And kept asking why, in my youth,

331
00:11:33,659 --> 00:11:35,019
I didn't go professional.

332
00:11:35,980 --> 00:11:37,860
Director Xiong was chasing you?

333
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:39,539
He was afraid you'd stiff him.

334
00:11:39,899 --> 00:11:41,620
And not pay his fee.

335
00:11:42,220 --> 00:11:42,919
Exactly.

336
00:11:42,919 --> 00:11:43,899
That's not true.

337
00:11:44,220 --> 00:11:45,460
Director Xiong came to our community,

338
00:11:45,460 --> 00:11:46,860
As a public service.

339
00:11:46,860 --> 00:11:47,980
He doesn't charge.

340
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,259
You're just crying sour grapes.

341
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:52,340
Our Changqing House is in the finals.

342
00:11:52,539 --> 00:11:54,480
Your Yannian House was eliminated.

343
00:11:55,460 --> 00:11:57,740
What's so great about the finals?

344
00:11:58,059 --> 00:12:00,460
Does being in the finals mean you'll win?

345
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:03,460
You never know.

346
00:12:03,980 --> 00:12:05,379
Say, if you happen to get

347
00:12:05,379 --> 00:12:07,059
A judge with bad eyesight,

348
00:12:07,379 --> 00:12:08,820
You might actually win.

349
00:12:08,899 --> 00:12:11,059
Bad eyesight... it's possible.

350
00:12:12,620 --> 00:12:14,539
We entered to win.

351
00:12:14,539 --> 00:12:15,820
Making the finals this time,

352
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,440
We must take the crown.

353
00:12:22,419 --> 00:12:23,539
Am I right?

354
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:25,740
Calls have dropped off, right?

355
00:12:26,179 --> 00:12:27,899
As long as you say you're out of town.

356
00:12:28,259 --> 00:12:29,399
The calls have decreased.

357
00:12:29,659 --> 00:12:30,740
But what about my royalties?

358
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:31,940
Royalties, royalties again.

359
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:33,740
We'll talk later.

360
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:35,340
You're not in a rush to spend it.

361
00:12:35,980 --> 00:12:37,500
I planned to take these royalties,

362
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,440
And donate them to my alma mater.

363
00:12:38,620 --> 00:12:39,899
Is your alma mater in a rush?

364
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,220
Then I'll advance it for you.

365
00:12:43,539 --> 00:12:44,500
Tell me how much you need.

366
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:46,340
Not much, just around fifty thousand.

367
00:12:46,460 --> 00:12:47,700
How much will you advance me?

368
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:48,740
I can...

369
00:12:49,820 --> 00:12:51,100
Make your alma mater wait.

370
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:54,620
Just focus on finishing the manuscript.

371
00:12:54,620 --> 00:12:55,659
Don't get distracted.

372
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:02,580
Hello? Who is this?

373
00:13:03,379 --> 00:13:04,299
Oh, Lao Qian.

374
00:13:04,539 --> 00:13:05,779
Say you're out of town.

375
00:13:06,539 --> 00:13:07,500
Say you're out...

376
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:08,059
No...

377
00:13:08,059 --> 00:13:09,940
No, I mean, I'm out of town.

378
00:13:10,740 --> 00:13:12,100
In Chengde, Hebei.

379
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:13,500
What?

380
00:13:14,059 --> 00:13:15,139
You're in Chengde too?

381
00:13:15,779 --> 00:13:17,059
This is all your "great" idea.

382
00:13:17,059 --> 00:13:18,500
He's in Chengde too. What do I do?

383
00:13:19,820 --> 00:13:21,379
Don't say you're in the city center.

384
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,460
Say you're in a county within Chengde.

385
00:13:24,779 --> 00:13:26,480
I'm not in Chengde city right now.

386
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:28,980
I'm in a certain...

387
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:30,539
Which county?

388
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:33,440
Longhua County.

389
00:13:33,659 --> 00:13:35,759
Where the hero Dong Cunrui sacrificed himself.

390
00:13:37,179 --> 00:13:38,580
I'm in Longhua County.

391
00:13:39,139 --> 00:13:41,299
The place where the hero Dong Cunrui died.

392
00:13:41,659 --> 00:13:43,500
No... Yes, it is that place.

393
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:44,500
What?

394
00:13:44,779 --> 00:13:45,940
You're in Longhua County too?

395
00:13:47,279 --> 00:13:48,299
Darn it.

396
00:13:48,299 --> 00:13:50,740
No, I mean, what a coincidence.

397
00:13:51,659 --> 00:13:52,580
How is this possible?

398
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:54,500
You've really screwed me over.

399
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:55,340
No...

400
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:56,940
I mean, my socks need mending.

401
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,059
Where am I staying?

402
00:13:59,220 --> 00:14:01,460
I'm staying at the County Guesthouse.

403
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:02,620
What?

404
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:04,059
You're at the County Guesthouse too?

405
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:05,740
Then...

406
00:14:06,059 --> 00:14:08,059
I'm in room 407.

407
00:14:09,220 --> 00:14:10,460
You're in 307?

408
00:14:10,659 --> 00:14:12,019
You absolutely must not come up.

409
00:14:12,019 --> 00:14:12,779
I'm not in.

410
00:14:13,419 --> 00:14:15,100
No, I mean, right now...

411
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,200
I'm not in the room.

412
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:18,179
I'm out at a meeting.

413
00:14:18,179 --> 00:14:19,019
It'll go on until very late.

414
00:14:19,019 --> 00:14:20,259
I won't be back until midnight.

415
00:14:22,059 --> 00:14:23,580
You want to treat me to a late-night snack?

416
00:14:23,580 --> 00:14:24,299
No need.

417
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:25,019
Really, no need.

418
00:14:25,019 --> 00:14:27,019
I'm not being polite, no.

419
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:29,940
Let's leave it at that for now, okay?

420
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:30,700
I'm in the meeting right now.

421
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,860
I have to speak soon.

422
00:14:32,059 --> 00:14:33,100
I'm hanging up now.

423
00:14:36,659 --> 00:14:37,820
Why are you glaring at me?

424
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:40,259
I didn't expect such a coincidence either.

425
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:41,740
So tell me, what should I do now?

426
00:14:41,740 --> 00:14:43,379
He insists on treating me to a late-night snack.

427
00:14:43,899 --> 00:14:44,700
What do I do?

428
00:14:45,379 --> 00:14:46,259
What do I do?

429
00:14:48,659 --> 00:14:50,100
Go to Longhua now.

430
00:14:50,659 --> 00:14:52,659
Anyway, Longhua isn't too far from Beijing.

431
00:14:53,019 --> 00:14:54,659
If you leave now, you can still make it.

432
00:14:54,820 --> 00:14:55,820
You want me to travel all that way?

433
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:57,500
Just to eat a late-night snack?

434
00:14:58,419 --> 00:14:58,899
I...

435
00:14:58,899 --> 00:14:59,700
What about my manuscript?

436
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:00,679
What about it?

437
00:15:00,899 --> 00:15:01,899
You tell me what to do.

438
00:15:02,340 --> 00:15:04,080
Now you're asking me what to do?

439
00:15:07,019 --> 00:15:08,779
No choice, I guess I have to go.

440
00:15:09,419 --> 00:15:10,460
So annoying. Let me tell you...

441
00:15:10,539 --> 00:15:11,820
You can't blame this on me.

442
00:15:12,059 --> 00:15:12,860
Chengde...

443
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:14,500
You were the one who said it first.

444
00:15:14,740 --> 00:15:16,139
If you hadn't said Chengde,

445
00:15:16,179 --> 00:15:18,500
we wouldn't be dealing with Longhua now, right?

446
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:22,940
Forgot my computer.

447
00:15:23,799 --> 00:15:24,460
Right.

448
00:15:29,779 --> 00:15:31,019
Don't forget your ID card.

449
00:15:31,580 --> 00:15:32,379
True.

450
00:15:36,179 --> 00:15:37,059
Don't forget to bring...

451
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:39,820
What else?

452
00:15:40,539 --> 00:15:41,779
Don't forget to bring...

453
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:44,779
Bring back some local specialties.

454
00:15:44,779 --> 00:15:45,460
Bah!

455
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,240
I just don't understand

456
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,919
why you insist on staying in room 407.

457
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,080
This room...

458
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,200
This place...

459
00:16:04,340 --> 00:16:05,720
It's shady and leaks rain.

460
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:07,399
The AC is broken.

461
00:16:07,399 --> 00:16:09,159
The toilet is clogged too.

462
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,279
The TV has issues too.

463
00:16:11,519 --> 00:16:14,240
And the internet cuts in and out.

464
00:16:14,519 --> 00:16:16,799
Someone can't come fix it until tomorrow.

465
00:16:20,399 --> 00:16:21,639
You staying in this room...

466
00:16:21,679 --> 00:16:23,159
isn't it inconvenient?

467
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:25,519
Well...

468
00:16:26,559 --> 00:16:27,679
that's because...

469
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,879
I stayed in this room three years ago.

470
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,240
I'm attached to it.

471
00:16:31,399 --> 00:16:32,480
That can't be right.

472
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:33,399
Our guesthouse...

473
00:16:33,399 --> 00:16:35,320
only officially opened last year.

474
00:16:36,919 --> 00:16:38,240
Then I must have remembered wrong.

475
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:40,840
Seems my language arts still need polishing.

476
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,360
You go ahead and get busy.

477
00:16:42,399 --> 00:16:43,480
I'm going to rest a bit.

478
00:16:43,759 --> 00:16:44,600
Thanks a lot.

479
00:16:57,559 --> 00:16:58,360
Lao Qian.

480
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,600
I've arrived in Longhua.

481
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:04,440
I mean...

482
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,640
I'm back at the Longhua County guesthouse.

483
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,240
Why don't you come up?

484
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:11,160
To my room.

485
00:17:12,039 --> 00:17:12,759
Didn't you say...

486
00:17:12,759 --> 00:17:15,119
you'd treat me to a late-night snack tonight?

487
00:17:17,559 --> 00:17:18,359
What?

488
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,240
You're in Beijing?

489
00:17:21,119 --> 00:17:21,920
No...

490
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:23,039
Didn't you say...

491
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:27,039
Is that any way to joke around?

492
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:28,680
No...

493
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:31,359
No, how can I not be anxious?

494
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:33,359
I came all the way from Beijing...

495
00:17:34,599 --> 00:17:36,920
Forget it. We'll talk later.

496
00:17:42,759 --> 00:17:44,000
Shenzhou went to space.

497
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,079
The national football team clocked out.

498
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,119
Memorizing lines is easy...

499
00:17:48,119 --> 00:17:49,200
why can't I get this down?

500
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,200
The national football team...

501
00:17:51,119 --> 00:17:52,160
The national football team what?

502
00:17:54,359 --> 00:17:56,039
I don't believe I can't memorize this.

503
00:17:56,359 --> 00:17:57,160
The national football team...

504
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,480
Hello?

505
00:18:06,599 --> 00:18:07,559
Little Fan.

506
00:18:08,319 --> 00:18:09,400
How are things over there?

507
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:12,720
No...

508
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:14,680
How about this, I...

509
00:18:18,359 --> 00:18:20,079
Hey, can you listen to me for a second?

510
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:24,119
How was I supposed to know they were joking?

511
00:18:25,359 --> 00:18:27,119
Wasn't I doing it for your own good?

512
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:30,039
Just stay there and write in peace.

513
00:18:30,599 --> 00:18:31,359
You might as well stay in Longhua...

514
00:18:31,359 --> 00:18:33,200
and finish that book before coming back.

515
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:36,680
Blame me?

516
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:38,079
Can you really blame me?

517
00:18:38,599 --> 00:18:39,440
Honestly.

518
00:18:40,279 --> 00:18:41,359
Just stay there.

519
00:18:41,359 --> 00:18:43,559
Thinking of coming back... honestly.

520
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,119
I won't look, I just won't look.

521
00:18:49,279 --> 00:18:50,079
The national football team...

522
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:54,079
How can the national football team go to space?

523
00:19:22,339 --> 00:19:23,059
You're back.

524
00:19:27,180 --> 00:19:27,980
Out for a stroll?

525
00:19:33,579 --> 00:19:34,740
Second prize.

526
00:19:36,539 --> 00:19:38,180
Wasn't President Li determined to win?

527
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:40,059
Wasn't it first prize or nothing?

528
00:19:40,740 --> 00:19:42,140
As leaders, we...

529
00:19:42,859 --> 00:19:43,619
how can we...

530
00:19:43,619 --> 00:19:46,220
compete with the masses for titles and awards?

531
00:19:47,339 --> 00:19:48,660
Second prize is fine.

532
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:50,500
First prize...

533
00:19:51,259 --> 00:19:53,460
let Songhe Residence have it.

534
00:19:54,259 --> 00:19:55,740
President Li, your mindset...

535
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:57,099
is really quite elevated.

536
00:19:57,259 --> 00:19:58,299
I think...

537
00:19:58,579 --> 00:19:59,259
in this competition...

538
00:19:59,259 --> 00:20:00,980
if you hadn't played the male lead...

539
00:20:00,980 --> 00:20:01,700
maybe...

540
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,900
our Changqing Residence could have won first prize.

541
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:04,819
It's possible.

542
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:07,220
What do you mean by that?

543
00:20:07,420 --> 00:20:08,420
Exactly what I said.

544
00:20:09,380 --> 00:20:10,400
Always spouting nonsense.

545
00:20:10,779 --> 00:20:11,579
Come in.

546
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:15,980
Editor Song.

547
00:20:17,180 --> 00:20:17,980
Hello.

548
00:20:18,019 --> 00:20:19,259
Why did you bring gifts?

549
00:20:19,619 --> 00:20:22,180
You could have just sent a junior editor.

550
00:20:22,259 --> 00:20:24,220
Why come in person?

551
00:20:24,380 --> 00:20:25,599
Come, sit.

552
00:20:28,259 --> 00:20:29,059
Okay.

553
00:20:29,220 --> 00:20:30,259
Okay, thanks.

554
00:20:30,940 --> 00:20:32,099
You received the manuscript, right?

555
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,019
We received it.

556
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:36,779
I'm sorry, Mr. Fan.

557
00:20:37,059 --> 00:20:38,940
I heard that to rush this draft...

558
00:20:38,940 --> 00:20:40,099
you worked yourself sick.

559
00:20:41,619 --> 00:20:42,740
Just a minor ailment.

560
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,539
Our agency leadership instructed me...

561
00:20:45,779 --> 00:20:47,180
to come visit you specifically...

562
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:49,619
and express our apologies.

563
00:20:51,099 --> 00:20:52,259
You're too kind.

564
00:20:53,059 --> 00:20:54,299
I'm the one who should apologize.

565
00:20:54,859 --> 00:20:56,140
I rushed as fast as I could...

566
00:20:56,140 --> 00:20:57,259
but was still three days late.

567
00:20:57,259 --> 00:20:58,440
I must have delayed your work.

568
00:20:58,700 --> 00:20:59,779
Not at all.

569
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:03,380
That you could finish the manuscript in ten days...

570
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:05,940
the young editors in our agency...

571
00:21:06,380 --> 00:21:08,019
all say you have god-like speed.

572
00:21:08,339 --> 00:21:09,220
Nowadays...

573
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:11,859
only a highly respected...

574
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:13,220
old-school scholar like you...

575
00:21:13,299 --> 00:21:15,440
could possibly submit the draft half a month early.

576
00:21:18,420 --> 00:21:19,220
What?

577
00:21:20,579 --> 00:21:21,380
Early?

578
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:23,180
Didn't you ask me...

579
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:24,940
within one week...

580
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,380
to finish the manuscript?

581
00:21:27,299 --> 00:21:28,099
No.

582
00:21:28,140 --> 00:21:29,180
What we said was...

583
00:21:29,460 --> 00:21:31,539
just finish it within a month.

584
00:21:31,779 --> 00:21:32,619
A month?

585
00:21:33,059 --> 00:21:36,140
You just need to finish your manuscript within a week.

586
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:37,460
There's absolutely no rush.

587
00:21:41,839 --> 00:21:42,559
Lao Li!

588
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:45,740
Li Jianguo!

589
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:46,740
Get back here!
